Standard Development Rules (SDR):
Here's set of rules that you must consider while developing this project

Style and Decoration:
- use line of "=" to seperate distict logic areas 
- use line of "-" to seperate sections of the same logic area

- follow my comments style, adding ? mark to make some lines blue. add the comments to explain the main idea of a block of code 



Naming Conventions

- Avoid introducing randomness or unexplained variability

- Use descriptive, domain-driven names

- Avoid abbreviations unless universally understood

- Match existing naming conventions in the repository





Backend Rules:

- Respect layered architecture (service → controller → routes → app → server )


TypeScript Usage

- Avoid "any" as type




Documentation Rules:

- Update documentation(ReadMe file) when behavior changes



